==English==

===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{bor|en|la|incrementum}}, from {{m|la|incrēscō}} (whence {{m|en|increase}}), from {{m|la|in-}} + {{m|la|crēscō||grow}}. Equivalent to {{suffix|en|increase|ment}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˈɪŋkɹɪmn̩t/}}
** {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Vealhurl-increment.wav|Audio (UK)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The action of [[increasing]] or becoming greater.
#* {{RQ:Woodward Natural History|passage=the seminary that furnisheth matter for the formation and '''increment''' of animal and vegetable bodies}}
#* '''June 9, 1832''' {{w|Samuel Taylor Coleridge}}, ''Table Talk''
#*: A nation, to be great, ought to be compressed in its '''increment''' by nations more civilized than itself.
# {{lb|en|heraldry}} The [[wax|waxing]] of the moon.
# The [[amount]] of [[increase]].
#* {{quote-journal|en|year=1941|month=June|author=Cecil J. Allen|title=British Locomotive Practice and Performance|journal=Railway Maagazine|page=263|text=In the third place, the superelevation and alignment of the track, theoretically calculated for speeds of 70 to 75 m.p.h., was adequate for the 80 to 85 m.p.h. or so normally attained as maxima over the G.N. main line; but nothing whatever had been done to prepare it for the enormous '''increment''' over these figures that this run was to produce.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2020|author=[[w:Brandon Taylor (writer)|Brandon Taylor]]|title=[[w:Real Life (novel)|Real Life]]|publisher=Daunt Books Originals|page=90|passage=The others will return at night, [...] pushing their experiments and nudging their projects toward completion in small, painful '''increments'''.}}
# {{lb|en|rhetoric}} An [[amplification]] without strict [[climax]], as in the following passage: "Finally, brethren, whatsoever things are true, whatsoever things are honest, whatsoever things are just, whatsoever things are pure, whatsoever things are lovely, whatsoever things are of good report, {{...}} think on these things."
# {{lb|en|chess}} The amount of time added to a player's clock after each move.
# {{lb|en|grammar}} A [[syllable]] in excess of the number of the nominative singular or the second-person singular present indicative.

